<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08111j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08111j">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08111j"> 111(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Septem = valde / 7 days</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><i>Ita locum intellexit interpres Arabs qui vertit: punietur valde. Solet enim numerus septem vel septuplum in Scriptura passim poni ad indefinitam multitudinem, magnitudinem, copiam, alicujus rei indicandam.</i> <br><font color="green">[Thus an Arabian interpreter and translater has understood the passage: he will be punished exceedingly. It is usual in the Scripture that the number seven or multiples of seven everywhere are taken down to indicate an indefinite large number, amplitude, abundance of something.]</font> <small> Thomas Josephus Lamy, <a name="TJLC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#TJLC"><cite title="source">Commentarium in librum geneseos</cite></a> (1884) 256</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
